items.text: What a great find. Feels like in Australia. Wholesome food with an easy vibe. For something light, don't miss the quinoa salad or the granola yogurt. For something heavier, try the smoked mackerel!
Anything with Avocado. Super fresh! Coffee is up there as well.
They have dinner now! Less people on weeknights and great attentive service.
At first glance, the menu looks limited. But when you discover all the combinations you can create with the side dishes -> galore! I got the ricotta w/ avocado, no nuts, added side of smoked salmon.
Dinner is served here, but be prepared to wait a bit. The beef with mash was awesome.
Lobster sandwich
Coffee & breakfast
Coffee is great. One of the few places serving the Cortado. For Breakfast, "Pimp your own" is the way to go. I wish they had more "put together for you" selections, though.
The French Toast is amazing
Get slayed at Sarnies' sister cafe. The latest slayer machine pulls your shots & for the most part, they are good. Pumpkin salad is VERY filling and the panini delicious BUT very messy.
Lobster Roll! Hard to find good ones around.
apart from the visually appealing slayer coffee machine, the food was overpriced & service deplorable. gr8 ambience for a cuppa & cake, not for a real meal
Lovely coffee .
Incredibly good Sunday roast (available after 11am). Chunky slices of beer, delicious truffled mash with gravy, and sautéed vegetables.
Poor service. Staff stood around and harassed us to leave.
One of the best bacons in town. It's toasted but it's damn crispy unlike other cafes after toasting the bacons it kinda hard to chew.
Ricotta cheese
Pretty good brunch food. Coffee not recommended - brunt & sour taste.
The food is not very fantastic.
I love this place! The ambiance is very pleasant. Friendly people and good coffee. Had the tiramisu during my visit. Was one of the best i had. Portion is huge too! Couldn't finish it myself.
On the pricey side, sausages could be better but decent food & coffee on the whole.
Tried a few of their servings. The French toast was awesome! Not your average French toast. Tried the daily specialty as well, spicy pork baked eggs. I thought the pork tasted like chicken.
Breakfast,,,
Awesome service! Food a bit pricey for the size but taste is great! Almost always crowded though. Nice nooks to chill with ur cuppa.
Their (holy!) mackerel & sumptuous salmon plate looks æ (that word). Had a latté.
Really good piccolo! Try their house smoked salmon! They also make butter and peanut butter at home!
Chilled out cafe
Customisable all day breakfasts, fantastic if you have allergies, are gluten free or low carb etc.
They reckon they are the "Best coffee in town". U reckon?
Nice space, slick slayer machine and impressive food menu items. Definitely worth visiting!
LCHF people! Perfect place to indulge in brunch without the carbs!
If offered a seat at the counter, reject it unless you like people behind & beside you try to settle their bills. Avoid seats by the entrance unless you like warm blasts of air & curious patrons.
This place smokes its meats onsite, and you can tell; get the platter and smile all day.
Food for four
Coffee is good. Definitely pimp your breakfast and pale ale!
Coffee roast is a little light for me but the food is brilliant. Quality produce, executed perfectly. Keep it simple: pimp your brekkie.
Waste of time. Buttermilk pancakes were sour with sour berries and sour ricotta. Gross
Anything is good here and it's particularly great for brunch
Decent food and coffee, great atmosphere. The hand cut chips with their burgers are great! They have dinner menu now!
Second chance for the Lokal. 10' to get a cappuccino and there are only 3 tables to serve (mostly done w lunch).chocolate cookie taste too much baking powder. I'm sure there are better places around.
Aussie cafe feel. Great coffee!
Service is excellent. Really chilled environment. Coffee here is a little sour and not my favourite. Sourdough toast was lovely with wilted spinach and scrambled eggs. Fresh juice is excellent!
Service is weird. You have to order up front and pay and they bring out the food. Quality of service is sub par, likely bc of busy crowd tho there should be no excuses. Not worth a return.
Smoked salmon. Mackerel. Coffee
Great coffee. Strong WiFi signal. No problem even video calling via Skype!
The locale is very chill... Many were having meetings, laptops were out! Staff was friendly. The cold teas were not overly sweet and refreshing and their sticky date was superb!!
Вкусная еда, приятная атмосфера! Возвращались сюда несколько раз!
Beware of the free WiFi provider The Lokal is using. Read the T&C; the info you provide (e-mail and mobile number) will be used for marketing purposes.
Homemade ricotta with fresh avocado. Could have done with more crushed nuts and pomelo. Order a side of sausage for a good measure.
Sunday roast at $28 was great value - thick slab of roast beef!
Toast of the day was very nice. Banana bread was pretty average. Coffee was decent
Coffee was too light and milky. Common man coffee is way better! Food portion was huge thou but slightly expensive.
Sticky date pudding is good! Great hospitality too 👍
I recommend you to build your own breakfast/brunch plate if you can't decide what to get from the menu! Don't overload on the sides though - 4 sides come up to about $16
Good salads
Build your own breakfast! Avocado mash 😊
The Lokal will start serving dinners  from 11 November 2014. Here's A preview...
Lovely space, I don't really remember the food items to be honest.  But I do remember the piccolo cos it knocked my socks off! Exactly how I like it. Fragrant, smooth and not too bitter.
Great service and food. Coffee is impeccable.
Kind of pricy but decent healthy food. Love the homemade ricotta with honey.
Best to do a reservation as this place is always packed during peak hours. Spicy pork baked eggs, a specialty dish on the board. Rather spicy. The pork was so juicy, I thought it tasted like chicken.
Lovely addition to the area, chilled atmo and great tubes. Recommending breakfast!
Improvements need to be made on that bun for the breakfast burger. Otherwise, pretty good pork belly. Lovely ambience.
Perfectly balanced cold brew
Excellent breakfast, good portions. Toastie was chock full of cheese & ham. Grilled mushrooms perfectly done as was the mackerel; they smoke it in-house. Coffee apparently decent too. Two thumbs up!
Come during lunch time if u want to be totally ignored for 10 mins
Homemade butter, ricotta, bacon, kimchi. Regular brunch menus far improved with artistry and dedication. Gets packed so arrive early and get in line (they text you when it's your turn)
Dot take the hot chocolate. Too watery and definitely not hot.
This is the place for breakfast. A few options on the brunch menu but best to make your own. Bacon and sausage is killer and the service is super prompt.
Awesome breakfast menu. Reminds me of Reuben hills
Returned twice since my previous tip for food and can say it is much better than the coffee. Particularly partial to the breakfast offerings.
Can't comment on the food. Popped in for a coffee and the double espresso I received after a slightly longer wait than should be necessary wasn't bad, but wasn't great either.
Service sucks juice is tiny serving and baked eggs dry as hell couldnt even swallow it down
The cold brew is amazeball
